-- Toyota hopes for U.S. market recovery end of 2009
-- 
-- Thu Nov 6, 2008 5:39am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/11/06/us-toyota-usa-idUSTRE4A51NS20081106

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Toyota Motor Corp said on Thursday the automaker hopes to see a turnaround in the U.S. car market around the end of 2009. 

 "We're hoping for a recovery around the end of next year," Executive Vice President Mitsuo Kinoshita told a news conference. Toyota also said it was revising its 2009 sales forecasts and that the figures would be "very severe." (Reporting by  Chang-Ran Kim )